@startuml agent-authoring-context
title AKDB Agent-Authoring - System Context
left to right direction
actor "Coding agent" as Agent
actor "Architecture maintainer" as Human
rectangle "AKDB agent-authoring subsystem" as Subsystem
rectangle "CLI / FastAPI / MCP surfaces" as Surfaces
database "AKDB knowledge database\nSQLite or PostgreSQL" as DB
folder "Registered repositories\nread-only evidence" as Repos
rectangle "Optional embedding endpoint" as Embeddings
rectangle "Tiny Tool Observatory\nand other consumers" as Consumers
Agent --> Surfaces : recall, explore, author, review
Human --> Surfaces : curate, validate, release
Surfaces --> Subsystem
Subsystem --> DB : project-scoped knowledge graph
Subsystem --> Repos : provenance and file mapping reads
Subsystem --> Embeddings : optional semantic vectors
Subsystem --> Consumers : compact API/MCP results or exports
note bottom
Consumers remain outside this repository's data boundary.
AKDB owns only its code, architecture and explicitly authored knowledge.
end note
@enduml
